The paper discusses generalization error bounds for deep neural networks, which is a topic closely related to machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new characterization of the Lipschitz properties of neural network family, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the generalization bounds for popular architectures such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and residual networks (ResNets), which are specific topics in neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY).
